response:
If you think you may have thalassemia, and if your parents have it, you should see a doctor.
You’ll take simple blood tests. One is a CBC (complete blood count) test. The other is a haemoglobin electrophoresis test. If you are pregnant or trying to have a baby, and both you and your partner are thalassemia carrier, there are tests that can be done before birth to learn if the baby will have the condition.
If you do have thalassemia, you should see a blood expert known as a haematologist. You may also need other special doctors on your team, like those who treat the heart or liver.
